1
00:00:55,550 --> 00:00:59,080
MY DEAREST NEMEZIS

2
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:09,700
We were headed to my favorite anime event.

3
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:12,900
after pleading with my busy parents.

4
00:01:16,990 --> 00:01:18,190
Are you happy, son?

5
00:01:18,690 --> 00:01:23,790
Yes. All the fans will come to this event today.

6
00:01:24,690 --> 00:01:27,860
You'll be even more excited when you see this.

7
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,620
- Ta-da! - Wow.

8
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:05,330
Mama...

9
00:02:07,020 --> 00:02:08,220
Mama.

10
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:10,130
Can you hear me?

11
00:02:12,150 --> 00:02:16,040
Mom, mom, mom!

12
00:02:18,140 --> 00:02:19,260
Oci!

13
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:21,220
Oci!

14
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:25,150
Here! Here! Quick!

15
00:02:25,950 --> 00:02:27,420
People are injured.

16
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,440
Out of the way, out of the way.

17
00:02:29,910 --> 00:02:30,750
Are you okay?

18
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,920
My parents protected me,

19
00:03:08,420 --> 00:03:09,860
but they died.

20
00:03:16,740 --> 00:03:18,200
Mama.

21
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,070
Oci.

22
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:25,790
Ban Ju Yeon, stop crying.

23
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:30,550
You have no right to cry.

24
00:03:32,050 --> 00:03:33,390
My son wouldn't die,

25
00:03:33,990 --> 00:03:36,540
if it weren't for you.

26
00:03:38,670 --> 00:03:40,570
The guests will be arriving soon. Get up.

27
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,080
What about the order I gave you, Secretary Kwon?

28
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,990
I contacted all the media.

29
00:03:55,090 --> 00:03:56,350
They said they would comply.

30
00:03:56,450 --> 00:03:59,670
Make sure the value of the shares does not fall.

31
00:03:59,970 --> 00:04:00,810
I see.

32
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:13,940
Since the day I lost my parents,

33
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:17,020
I became my grandmother's scapegoat.

34
00:04:17,620 --> 00:04:20,980
I told you to handle it yourself.

35
00:04:21,580 --> 00:04:22,670
What?

36
00:04:23,770 --> 00:04:24,330
What?

37
00:04:45,270 --> 00:04:47,810
MEMORIAL DAY FOR MOTHER AND FATHER

38
00:05:29,750 --> 00:05:31,010
If it weren't for me...

39
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:39,710
It's my fault.

40
00:05:46,630 --> 00:05:47,810
But I wasn't the only one,

41
00:05:48,810 --> 00:05:52,310
who lost loved ones that day.

42
00:06:01,380 --> 00:06:02,180
I will take over.

43
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:05,600
my father's place.

44
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,540
I did everything in my power,

45
00:06:09,640 --> 00:06:10,900
to become what my grandmother wanted me to be.

46
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,330
But the more I tried, the lonelier I became.

47
00:06:13,530 --> 00:06:16,760
She took away the things I relied on.

48
00:06:19,100 --> 00:06:20,770
Like a dragon hiding in a cave

49
00:06:21,170 --> 00:06:23,700
and seeks solace in loneliness,

50
00:06:24,300 --> 00:06:25,580
I needed my cave,

51
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:28,940
my utopia that no one can disturb.

52
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:22,230
PART 4

53
00:07:22,330 --> 00:07:23,450
It looks so real.

54
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:26,740
What are you doing?

55
00:07:27,740 --> 00:07:29,140
Good day, Mr. Director.

56
00:07:29,940 --> 00:07:31,030
It's funny to see you like this.

57
00:07:31,130 --> 00:07:32,090
What are you doing here?

58
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:34,140
Don't you think I should ask?

59
00:07:34,240 --> 00:07:37,540
You decorated your room very nicely.

60
00:07:38,340 --> 00:07:39,920
You claimed you didn't have such a hobby.

61
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:41,490
Does this look like my room?

62
00:07:41,890 --> 00:07:43,060
It's my nephew's room.

63
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:45,720
- Nephew? - Nephew.

64
00:07:45,820 --> 00:07:47,460
I am not like those

65
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:49,840
who like to lock themselves in their rooms.

66
00:07:50,140 --> 00:07:51,380
I'm just being kind and...

67
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:54,180
I love music and comics.

68
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:57,110
Remember that.

69
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:01,340
- Okay. - Go away.

70
00:08:01,640 --> 00:08:03,770
I only work with top professionals.

71
00:08:04,170 --> 00:08:06,340
I'm here for work. I need to get it done.

72
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:08,240
I'm not as good as my father,

73
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:09,720
but I'm an expert.

74
00:08:11,420 --> 00:08:13,120
Things to fix are there, right?

75
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:18,640
Be careful! Don't break it.

76
00:08:18,740 --> 00:08:21,240
I waited forever for them to put it in stock.

77
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:22,530
Excuse me?

78
00:08:25,660 --> 00:08:26,520
My nephew was waiting.

79
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:29,670
My nephew waited a long time.

80
00:08:30,770 --> 00:08:32,230
He would be upset, you know?

81
00:08:33,230 --> 00:08:36,870
Your nephew is very impatient.

82
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:40,280
Could uncle wait a moment too?

83
00:08:40,380 --> 00:08:42,340
I will definitely fix it.

84
00:08:57,780 --> 00:08:58,990
What is he really thinking?

85
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,850
Don't be nervous, Ban Ju Yeon. Get over it.

86
00:09:04,950 --> 00:09:06,960
Be alert even during a crisis.

87
00:09:50,100 --> 00:09:52,150
Can you play it that loud?

88
00:09:52,350 --> 00:09:54,030
Your neighbor will be angry.

89
00:09:54,230 --> 00:09:55,830
I soundproofed the room.

90
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:58,540
It's like being at a concert.

91
00:10:00,680 --> 00:10:01,450
What did you say?

92
00:10:03,790 --> 00:10:06,010
You have a fun life.

93
00:10:06,810 --> 00:10:08,270
This room must be yours...

94
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:21,530
What are you doing?

95
00:10:22,930 --> 00:10:23,710
It was a mistake.

96
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,510
My nephew and I like the same music.

97
00:11:00,610 --> 00:11:01,990
That child looks a lot like me.

98
00:11:04,900 --> 00:11:06,800
I see.

99
00:11:19,020 --> 00:11:19,640
Stop!

100
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:22,590
Are you crazy? Why are you grabbing my things...

101
00:11:22,690 --> 00:11:24,000
Why are you touching this?

102
00:11:26,010 --> 00:11:28,830
This is the first edition from 1996.

103
00:11:31,710 --> 00:11:32,700
And what about this...

104
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,900
Special edition released in 2001.

105
00:11:37,100 --> 00:11:37,720
A toto?

106
00:11:38,620 --> 00:11:41,190
This is a signed copy. It is my precious...

107
00:11:45,090 --> 00:11:46,080
I knew it.

108
00:11:46,980 --> 00:11:48,890
It doesn't belong to the imaginary nephew.

109
00:11:48,990 --> 00:11:50,550
It belongs to you.

110
00:11:50,950 --> 00:11:52,370
All these things.

111
00:11:53,370 --> 00:11:55,460
I have a nephew.

112
00:11:55,560 --> 00:11:56,520
You are an only child.

113
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:57,800
You have no relatives.

114
00:12:02,760 --> 00:12:05,290
So? What exactly do you want?

115
00:12:05,990 --> 00:12:09,060
Let's say this is my room and I like all these things.

116
00:12:10,360 --> 00:12:11,590
Will that change anything?

117
00:12:13,290 --> 00:12:14,180
It will change.

118
00:12:15,780 --> 00:12:17,020
You forgot the contract.

119
00:12:17,120 --> 00:12:19,200
You like both rock bands and comics.

120
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:21,620
You like many more things,

121
00:12:22,420 --> 00:12:24,360
as I thought.

122
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:27,770
My perception has changed.

123
00:12:28,970 --> 00:12:31,460
I learned a lot more about you.

124
00:13:04,990 --> 00:13:05,760
Are you okay?

125
00:13:24,970 --> 00:13:26,640
I sent the money to your father's account.

126
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:27,910
Thank you.

127
00:13:30,340 --> 00:13:31,220
Also

128
00:13:32,520 --> 00:13:33,310
tie...

129
00:13:34,610 --> 00:13:36,200
clothes. You know.

130
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:41,320
If you don't want to return them on Monday, you could...

131
00:13:41,420 --> 00:13:44,770
That's fine. Why would you sell a gift?

132
00:13:47,570 --> 00:13:49,330
Was it a gift?

133
00:14:05,530 --> 00:14:06,300
Hello?

134
00:14:08,670 --> 00:14:10,180
Yes, he is my father.

135
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:12,400
HOSPITAL?

136
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:15,540
I'll be right back.

137
00:14:16,540 --> 00:14:17,510
I'm going now.

138
00:14:17,910 --> 00:14:20,060
- I'll give you a ride. - No, I can go alone.

139
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:22,550
If you rush, you could have an accident like I did.

140
00:14:23,050 --> 00:14:24,130
Let's go.

141
00:14:46,100 --> 00:14:47,610
The operation went well.

142
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:48,860
Some time

143
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,780
He won't be able to move because he broke his ankle.

144
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:54,240
We'll see how long he has to be hospitalized.

145
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:56,000
Sure. Thank you.

146
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:58,620
After waking up

147
00:14:58,720 --> 00:15:00,800
the patient will go to the VIP ward.

148
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,930
My father is not a VIP.

149
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:05,240
Yes, as. As a VIP.

150
00:15:05,340 --> 00:15:06,840
VVIP, to be exact.

151
00:15:08,140 --> 00:15:08,930
Double V.

152
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:11,950
Take us to the room.

153
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:15,680
Thank you.

154
00:15:18,220 --> 00:15:20,250
I told you not to overdo it.

155
00:15:20,550 --> 00:15:21,840
You've been doing extra work, haven't you?

156
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:24,090
No, he didn't.

157
00:15:24,190 --> 00:15:25,870
- You're lying. - I'm not lying.

158
00:15:28,330 --> 00:15:31,430
You must have been worried, sweetheart. I'm sorry.

159
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:33,890
Get well soon and return home.

160
00:15:34,890 --> 00:15:36,000
Would you like some beef bone broth?

161
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,460
I'll cook it for eight hours...

162
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:38,820
The food here is good.

163
00:15:40,020 --> 00:15:42,750
Probably yes.

164
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:45,680
Thank you for the special treatment.

165
00:15:45,780 --> 00:15:47,360
I don't know what to say.

166
00:15:47,660 --> 00:15:49,350
Yongsung je rodina.

167
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:51,430
I can't ignore a hurt family member.

168
00:15:51,530 --> 00:15:54,220
I have fulfilled my duty as a superior. Don't worry.

169
00:15:54,320 --> 00:15:55,870
Focus on your recovery.

170
00:15:56,770 --> 00:15:58,390
Yes, of course.

171
00:15:58,490 --> 00:16:02,190
I apologize for coming so late.

172
00:16:02,290 --> 00:16:03,420
I was impatient.

173
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:05,380
Team leader Baek is a key member.

174
00:16:05,780 --> 00:16:09,110
It's my fault that I have a talented daughter.

175
00:16:12,460 --> 00:16:13,460
I admire you.

176
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,760
Relax. I'll go.

177
00:16:19,290 --> 00:16:20,430
Wait, Dad.

178
00:16:29,010 --> 00:16:30,920
You must be close to your father.

179
00:16:32,580 --> 00:16:33,920
You could say it like that.

180
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:35,480
Thank you.

181
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:38,010
I would be worried if I were alone.

182
00:16:39,010 --> 00:16:41,620
Thanks to you, we can enjoy the VIP section.

183
00:16:41,720 --> 00:16:42,790
It's nice.

184
00:16:49,450 --> 00:16:50,070
What?

185
00:16:50,870 --> 00:16:52,100
You smile a lot.

186
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:55,560
You don't usually smile.

187
00:16:58,550 --> 00:16:59,550
Let's not overdo it.

188
00:17:00,150 --> 00:17:01,440
You don't have to accompany me.

189
00:18:32,330 --> 00:18:34,370
This is Director Ban's phone number, right?

190
00:18:34,870 --> 00:18:36,550
Thank you for today.

191
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:37,920
Get home safely.

192
00:18:53,190 --> 00:18:53,700
Oci!

193
00:18:58,220 --> 00:18:58,970
Oci.

194
00:18:59,870 --> 00:19:01,690
You haven't met your future bride yet.

195
00:19:01,790 --> 00:19:03,030
You can't leave.

196
00:19:03,430 --> 00:19:04,720
I'll be good to you.

197
00:19:05,020 --> 00:19:07,230
I will pass the exam on the first try.

198
00:19:07,630 --> 00:19:08,520
Oci.

199
00:19:09,620 --> 00:19:10,930
Don't die, Dad.

200
00:19:12,230 --> 00:19:13,300
You heard him, Dad.

201
00:19:13,600 --> 00:19:14,040
What?

202
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:17,180
Are you serious, son?

203
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:20,250
Are you crazy, sister?

204
00:19:20,350 --> 00:19:21,600
You're more stupid.

205
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:22,710
Help your father.

206
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,920
How come you're in the VIP section?

207
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:33,670
You didn't win the lottery while I was away, did you?

208
00:19:33,770 --> 00:19:35,580
Did you also secretly move?

209
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:37,000
Is our apartment still there?

210
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:38,960
Father. Sister.

211
00:19:39,460 --> 00:19:40,590
You better be honest.

212
00:19:40,690 --> 00:19:42,030
God, you're noisy.

213
00:19:42,330 --> 00:19:43,980
Since when is he so talkative?

214
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,910
Try studying for the state exam.

215
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:47,370
I don't speak at all.

216
00:19:47,470 --> 00:19:49,410
I eat, sleep, and poop alone every day.

217
00:19:49,510 --> 00:19:52,060
Now I talk to teachers in videos.

218
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,170
I see.

219
00:19:53,370 --> 00:19:55,230
So how come you're in this department?

220
00:19:55,330 --> 00:19:56,680
Did you really win the lottery?

221
00:19:56,780 --> 00:19:58,160
Stocks? Cryptocurrency?

222
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:00,330
All my friends lost money.

223
00:20:00,630 --> 00:20:03,510
Su Jeongin's director furnished this room for me.

224
00:20:03,910 --> 00:20:04,630
Director?

225
00:20:05,430 --> 00:20:07,030
- Is it a man? - Yes.

226
00:20:07,530 --> 00:20:08,300
Are you dating?

227
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:10,390
- Are you crazy? - How old is he?

228
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:13,900
He looked very young. How old is he?

229
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:15,330
She's probably the same age as him.

230
00:20:15,430 --> 00:20:17,310
God, is he the same age?

231
00:20:17,410 --> 00:20:19,680
So he can't date you.

232
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:22,910
Why are you saying that? I don't like it.

233
00:20:23,010 --> 00:20:25,410
Someone my age wouldn't find you attractive.

234
00:20:25,610 --> 00:20:26,820
You are too old.

235
00:20:26,920 --> 00:20:27,510
What?

236
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:49,990
I left a gift for your father at the reception.

237
00:20:51,090 --> 00:20:52,030
Pick it up.

238
00:21:00,830 --> 00:21:01,640
Thank you.

239
00:21:09,250 --> 00:21:10,800
They are giving away stuffed animals.

240
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:12,240
Why would you want a stuffed animal?

241
00:21:12,440 --> 00:21:13,930
It's cute and free.

242
00:21:15,330 --> 00:21:17,800
Cute? That thing?

243
00:21:20,130 --> 00:21:21,670
He's really funny.

244
00:21:24,070 --> 00:21:24,780
Cute.

245
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:33,600
I've never seen a team leader take vacation.

246
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:37,010
I know. It's her first vacation since I got here.

247
00:21:37,210 --> 00:21:38,760
It's okay, right?

248
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,080
Should we call her?

249
00:21:41,460 --> 00:21:42,230
Hello.

250
00:21:43,230 --> 00:21:44,830
Representative Yun from the legal team.

251
00:21:45,150 --> 00:21:46,440
What brings you here?

252
00:21:46,540 --> 00:21:48,340
I saw a post on the company's website.

253
00:21:48,350 --> 00:21:49,360
I'm here to pick up my things.

254
00:21:51,970 --> 00:21:53,560
To...

255
00:21:53,660 --> 00:21:55,110
egg.

256
00:21:55,210 --> 00:21:56,920
Yes, a toy in an egg.

257
00:21:59,050 --> 00:22:01,630
Is it yours, Deputy Yun? Really?

258
00:22:01,730 --> 00:22:02,400
Yes.

259
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,050
It's my hobby to collect them.

260
00:22:07,020 --> 00:22:08,690
Is there a problem?

261
00:22:09,590 --> 00:22:10,820
- No, no. - No.

262
00:22:11,320 --> 00:22:12,360
It's unexpected.

263
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:14,880
Take care.

264
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:16,820
- Yes, goodbye. - Take care.

265
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:38,200
You left your tool bag with me.

266
00:22:38,900 --> 00:22:39,770
Do you need it?

267
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,150
Oci!

268
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:51,610
What? Why are you here?

269
00:22:51,910 --> 00:22:54,600
Why? You were here alone all weekend.

270
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:58,180
I'll be here from today. Go home.

271
00:22:58,980 --> 00:23:01,420
You're studying for an exam. You don't have time.

272
00:23:01,520 --> 00:23:03,530
You don't have time for this either.

273
00:23:03,730 --> 00:23:05,410
I can study here.

274
00:23:05,510 --> 00:23:06,820
It's more beautiful here than on my intranet.

275
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:09,670
Don't do anything stupid and study.

276
00:23:10,890 --> 00:23:12,400
You are not his only child.

277
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:15,430
- What? - I'm his son too.

278
00:23:16,530 --> 00:23:20,650
And how will we survive if you get sick too?

279
00:23:20,750 --> 00:23:23,360
You pay my tuition and rent.

280
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:27,420
I'll take care of him. Get some rest.

281
00:23:35,380 --> 00:23:36,740
So just stay today.

282
00:23:37,340 --> 00:23:39,520
I wanted to hire a nanny starting tomorrow.

283
00:23:39,720 --> 00:23:40,320
Okay.

284
00:23:42,040 --> 00:23:43,140
Don't leave him alone.

285
